The paper discusses the use of wireless sensor networks (WSNs) in various application domains, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also talks about virtualized WSNs, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of semantic applications and data annotation suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes an architecture that uses overlays, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
